{
  "stem": "11179.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I learned the concept of God very early, because I do remember when I-- when we went to lunch, to my grandmother's house one day, and my grandfather wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember asking where he was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She said-- she just told me, God took him with him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I accepted that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and it was nothing horrible in my eyes at the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was accepted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I meet people, even today, that want to keep death away from the children, not even tell them that the dog died, which I think is ridiculous.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't think it ever hurt me in my life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I never was-- talk about religious, I never was-- was-- was that religious, but I believed in God, and I believed God was something good.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's what I was taught.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "More in the liberal part of conservative.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, they did not keep a kosher household anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Also, I understand, my-- my great-grandparents, on one side, at least, did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they lived-- some of them lived in smaller towns before, and they were far more traditional.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In my grandparents' time, they lived in a big city, and they were not that traditional.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nevertheless, they were-- they were not bad Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I considered them, they were good Jews, because I don't think good and bad, in my opinion, has anything to do with being religious.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother had a passport to the zoo, and when-- and when she didn't have to work-- and we had a maid-- and-- and-- and she went-- the way I understand, and I remember, of course, some of it-- she went to the zoo with me, sometimes three, four times a week.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I played with neighbors' kids.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
